postcontent: This unmolested A.R. Davis over/under caplock muzzle loading rifle is very well preserved for its age. The walnut stock and brass are almost perfect. The locks and barrels have a brown patina finish with some speckling and minor surface pitting on the exterior of the barrels. The rifling is pronounced with only light surface oxidation. The only markings are on the top the barrel A.R. DAVIS DEPOSIT NY. Amos R Davis was a well known gunmaker in Deposit NY. He is mostly known for heavy barreled, large caliber, target grade rifles, with false muzzles and long range sights. Some of his rifles were used for "sniping" during the Civil War. Specifications: OVER/UNDER BARRELS: 24¼” octagon, measures .388” land-to-land, rate of twist unknown. STOCK: American walnut. LOP 12¾”. Tastefully contoured cheek piece with brass inlay. RAMRODS: Two, one mounted on each side between the barrels. LOCKS: Two, one for each barrel. TRIGGER: Adjustable trigger sequentially fires each lock. title: For Sale:  NEW Silencerco Osprey 9 Silencer Suppressor
postcontent: Check us out online!  www.54-17arms.com Brand new Silencerco Osprey 9 Silencer Suppressor. No credit card fees and shipping to your local FFL is FREE!  Price does not include the NFA tax stamp or local sales tax.  Also, with the purchase of this suppressor, we can assist you in creating a basic living trust!  A living trust will speed up the transfer process.  Let us know if you have questions.  SilencerCo’s Osprey family of pistol suppressors is a perfect blend of form and function. With the modern combat handgun in mind, SilencerCo set out to create a silencer that performs well and looks like it belongs—the best possible marriage between host weapon and silencer. SilencerCo went to work to make a suppressor that maximizes sound suppression levels, allows the use of more host pistols with factory sights, and has more operationally friendly features. What was created was the Osprey pistol silencer available for 9mm, .40 S&W, and 45ACP. Although round silencers are very effective for many applications, for a centerfire handgun round it has its limits. To obtain the most suppression, silencers must have as much internal volume as possible; but for a round tubular silencer, the only way to acquire more internal volume is by increasing the overall diameter and/or length. Increasing a tube’s diameter will obscure the site picture of the host gun and inhibit the possibility of holstering a weapon with the silencer still attached to the host gun. The Osprey is an eccentric silencer, which means that the bore does not run down the middle of the tube. Because of this eccentric design, most of the baffles and internal volume is beneath the centerline of the bore and out of the way of the gun’s sights, thus leaving the shooter the ability to use factory sights with little or no sight or target obstruction. The Osprey has flat side walls and angled edges that mimic many modern combat handgun slides and is just slightly wider than most host pistols. This feature allows the host weapon to be holstered with many popular open bottom holster designs with Osprey attached. The Osprey contains approximately 30% more internal volume than a traditional round tube silencer at the same length, but does so without obscuring the shooter’s sight picture or adding excessive width and length. 9 OSPREY CALIBER: 9MM Luger .300 BLK Subsonic WEIGHT: 9.8 OZ DIMENSIONS: 1.30”W × 1.75”H LENGTH: 7.0625” SOUND LEVEL: Dry: 125 dB (tested with a Sig 226 with American Eagle AE9FP 147 Grain Ammunition) FINISH: Hard Coat Anodizing Black Oxide MATERIALS: Core/Caps: 7075 T6 Aluminum Tube: 6061 T6 Aluminum Piston/Mounting System: 17-4 Stainless Steel, Heat Treated, Mount:Threads FEATURES: Interchangeable pistons Unobstructed sight picture Patented cam lock Mounting system Lifetime warranty MSRP: $849.95 (with piston)

title: For Sale:  NEW Silencerco Osprey 40 Silencer Suppressor With Piston
postcontent: Check us out online!  www.54-17arms.com Brand new Silencerco Osprey 40 Silencer Suppressor with the piston of your choice. No credit card fees and shipping to your local FFL is FREE!  Price does not include the NFA tax stamp or local sales tax.  Also, with the purchase of this suppressor, we can assist you in creating a basic living trust!  A living trust will speed up the transfer process.  Let us know if you have questions. SilencerCo’s Osprey family of pistol suppressors is a perfect blend of form and function. With the modern combat handgun in mind, SilencerCo set out to create a silencer that performs well and looks like it belongs—the best possible marriage between host weapon and silencer. SilencerCo went to work to make a suppressor that maximizes sound suppression levels, allows the use of more host pistols with factory sights, and has more operationally friendly features. What was created was the Osprey pistol silencer available for 9mm, .40 S&W, and 45ACP. Although round silencers are very effective for many applications, for a centerfire handgun round it has its limits. To obtain the most suppression, silencers must have as much internal volume as possible; but for a round tubular silencer, the only way to acquire more internal volume is by increasing the overall diameter and/or length. Increasing a tube’s diameter will obscure the site picture of the host gun and inhibit the possibility of holstering a weapon with the silencer still attached to the host gun. The Osprey is an eccentric silencer, which means that the bore does not run down the middle of the tube. Because of this eccentric design, most of the baffles and internal volume is beneath the centerline of the bore and out of the way of the gun’s sights, thus leaving the shooter the ability to use factory sights with little or no sight or target obstruction. The Osprey has flat side walls and angled edges that mimic many modern combat handgun slides and is just slightly wider than most host pistols. This feature allows the host weapon to be holstered with many popular open bottom holster designs with Osprey attached. The Osprey contains approximately 30% more internal volume than a traditional round tube silencer at the same length, but does so without obscuring the shooter’s sight picture or adding excessive width and length. 40 OSPREY CALIBER: 9MM - 40 S&W .300 BLK Subsonic WEIGHT: 11.1 OZ DIMENSIONS: 1.30”W × 1.75”H LENGTH: 8.0625” SOUND LEVEL: Dry: 130 dB (tested with a Glock 22 with Remington UMC 180 Grain Ammunition) FINISH: Hard Coat Anodizing Black Oxide MATERIALS: Core/Caps: 7075 T6 Aluminum Tube: 6061 T6 Aluminum Piston/Mounting System: 17-4 Stainless Steel, Heat Treated, Mount:Threads FEATURES: Interchangeable pistons Unobstructed sight picture Patented cam lock Mounting system Lifetime warranty MSRP: $849.95 (with piston)

title: For Sale/Trade:  Type 53 Mosin w/ ATI stock & Custom Iron Sights
location: Cape Coral, South West Florida, Florida
postcontent:
Shorter (than 91/30) length barrel is great for: blind or stand shooting, truck gun, ranch rifle, bush gun, and so on. The gun came with an old wooden stock with, shall we say, lots of character. The gouges and water marks lead me to believe it was used in less than preferable conditions (rice patties, rainfall etc). You don't know gun cleaning until you've cleaned one of these - caked and soaked in cosmoline and grit, it took about 2 hours of wiping, scrubbing, picking, crying, brushing, and finally heating it to force the cosmoline out of the pores.

Upgrades:
Last time I checked it shoots high, so after about a month or two of waiting my Smith Sights came in the mail (red fiber, and target post). Have yet to install them, scared of screwing it up. I'll take it out and make a decision.

Although I did clean, sand, and put a few coats of linseed oil on the original stock, I decided to put an ATI stock on it (left over from another mosin). Feels lighter, more comfortable, and looks slicker.

Added a comfortable sling (because reasons).

I took off the bayonet and ground off the lug because it: puts extra weight on the wrong end, disrupts barrel harmonics, is sharp, catches on everything, and looked ugly (in my opinion). The bayonets are cool, but this rifle is meant for throwing lead.

Not really an upgrade, but when I was disassembling it the bolt head shot past my face and disappeared into the wilderness that is my garage. Replacement bolt head with extractor is in the mail. 

You can't break this gun, the ammo is inexpensive and powerful, it's really fun (fireballs and loud bangs) and it handles well. 

I've got ammo to go with it.

In Cape Coral, FL

I also have a brand new Savage Hog Hunter 308 - comes with sling and ammo $480 (see "listings by this user" at top of page)
